---
title: Cheesy Sausage & Kale Flatbreads with Red Onion & Chili Flakes
description: Get ready to make delicious, foolproof, homemade flatbread pizza! And not just any pizza—these are sprinkled with mellow Monterey Jack and an Italian cheese blend, then topped with browned pork sausage and tender sautéed kale and red onion. Sprinkle your masterpiece with chili flakes, then broil until bubbly and dig right in!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6627cec62fa454163f211906-d6aaf856.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6627cec62fa454163f211906-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cheesy-sausage-kale-flatbreads-6627cec62fa454163f211906
time required: 20 minutes
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: North America
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 760 kcal
  fat: 42 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 63 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 41 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 2070 mg
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}; remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%oz}; chop into bite-size pieces.

Remove @Italian pork sausage mix{9%oz} from casing if necessary; discard casing.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add sausage and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add onion and kale (for 4 servings, you may need to add kale in batches); season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. (TIP: If pan seems dry, add another drizzle of oil.) Cook, stirring occasionally, until sausage is browned and cooked through, onion is tender, and kale is wilted, ~{4-6%minutes}.

While sausage and veggies cook, place @flatbreads{2} on a #baking sheet{} and toast on top rack until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}. (For 4 servings, divide between two baking sheets; toast on top and middle racks, swapping rack positions halfway through toasting.)

Once flatbreads are toasted, remove from oven. Carefully sprinkle evenly with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup} and @Italian cheese blend{1/2%cup}. Top with sausage and veggies. Sprinkle with @chili flakes{1%tsp} to taste.

Return flatbreads to top rack and bake until cheese melts, ~{2-4%minutes}. (For 4, return to top and middle racks.) Transfer flatbreads to a #cutting board{}.

Slice flatbreads into pieces.

Divide between plates and garnish with any remaining chili flakes if desired. Serve.

> Pork Sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.